input_full.title: Prepare repository for public SBSB tool release: remove SLS framework references from user-facing documentation
input_full.body:
User is preparing to share the Side-by-Side Blueprint (SBSB) tool with the Lean community later today. The repository needs to be prepared by hiding/removing all references to the SLS (Strange Loop Station) self-improvement framework that emerged around the core tool.

## Context

The project started as Side-by-Side Blueprint - a Lean documentation toolchain. The SLS self-improvement framework emerged from working on it. For the initial public release, the focus should be on the "level 1" tool (SBSB) to avoid overwhelming the audience with the meta-framework.

## Tasks

- [ ] Audit all user-facing documentation for SLS/Strange Loop Station references
- [ ] Remove or hide mentions of the SLS dev framework (both old and new names)
- [ ] Ensure documentation focuses on the blueprint tool itself
- [ ] Review README files, CLAUDE.md, and any other public-facing docs
- [ ] Verify CI/CD action documentation is clean
- [ ] Check showcase project READMEs (GCR, PNT, SBS-Test)

## Reference

Draft post outline: `dev/.refs/motivation2.txt`

Target audience: Lean community, including high-profile mathematicians. Post planned for later today.
